<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Transparent Taskbar like SiB]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5046&amp;p=21497#p21497"><![CDATA[
There is a tab in Classic Start Menu settings called &quot;Windows 10 Settings&quot;. There you can control if the Taskbar is opaque, transparent or glass. You can also adjust the opacity from 0 to 100. Also, if you use the Windows Aero skin or Windows 8 skin of the Classic Start Menu (Skins can be changed from the Skin tab), there is another setting on the &quot;Menu Look&quot; tab to control glass opacity of the right column. <br /><br />You could also try this extra skin which does not ship with Classic Shell: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://winaero.com/blog/get-the-best-looking-start-menu-for-classic-shell-4-with-winaero-skin-2-0/">http://winaero.com/blog/get-the-best-lo ... -skin-2-0/</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Tue Aug 25, 2015 9:59 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
